main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed near Palmdale, California on September 13, 1955.
interesting points: The object had a flat top and bottom with rounded ends, and was observed to have an exhaust or blast coming from the rear that was equal in width to the object.
The object made a constant sound described as a combination of a diesel roar and an afterburner roar, and moved very slowly.
The object was observed both visually from the ground and on radar, and its flight path was reported as west-southeast-south.
The duration of the observation was 10-15 minutes.
The report concludes that the object was possibly a test vehicle, but was ultimately listed as 'unknown'.
sighted object: a flat, rounded object with an exhaust or blast coming from the rear
